 the final step in making a check?', 'The GM compares the check result to the check DC and declares whether the check succeeds or fails.']\n['ABILITY MODIFIERS', 'How many ability modifiers are there in the game?', 'There are six ability modifiers: Strength (STR), Dexterity (DEX), Constitution (CON), Wisdom (WIS), Intelligence (INT), and Charisma (CHA).']\n['ABILITY MODIFIERS', 'What is the purpose of ability modifiers?', 'Ability modifiers are added to every check to determine the check result.']\n['ABILITY MODIFIERS', 'Who decides which ability modifier to use for a particular check?', 'The rules typically dictate which modifier to use, but in cases where no ability is listed, the GM decides which one is relevant.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What is the proficiency bonus?', 'The proficiency bonus is a bonus that all PCs and monsters have, which is determined by their level.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'How is the proficiency bonus used?', 'The proficiency bonus is added to a die roll or DC once, even if multiple rules allow you to add it to the same roll.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What happens if a circumstance suggests that your proficiency bonus applies more than once to the same roll?', 'You still add it only once and double or halve it only once.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', \"What happens if your proficiency bonus doesn't apply to a roll?\", \"Doubling your proficiency bonus doesn't change that.\"]\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What is the purpose of the proficiency bonus?', \"The proficiency bonus represents your character's skill and experience in various areas.\"]\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'Do monsters have a proficiency bonus?', 'Yes, monsters also have a proficiency bonus, which is incorporated into their stat blocks.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'Can you add your proficiency bonus to a roll if you lack proficiency in the relevant skill?', 'No, you can only add your proficiency bonus to a roll if you have proficiency in the relevant skill.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What happens if you have proficiency in multiple skills that apply to the same check?', 'You still only add your proficiency bonus once to the roll.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'Can you double your proficiency bonus on a roll?', 'Yes, some features or abilities may allow you to double your proficiency bonus on a roll.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What happens if you have disadvantage on a roll and a feature allows you to double your proficiency bonus?', 'You still only add your proficiency bonus once to the roll, even though you have disadvantage.\\n1']\n['DETERMINING SUCCESS OR FAILURE', 'How do you determine if a check succeeds or fails?', \"You measure your check result against a target number called a difficulty class (DC) set by the GM. If your check result is equal to or higher than the DC, you succeed. If it's less than the DC, you fail.\"]\n['DETERMINING DC', 'How is the DC determined?', 'Most of the time, the rules tell the GM what the DC should be. Sometimes the GM gets to set an appropriate number based on how hard they want a task to be.']\n['TYPICAL DIFFICULTY CLASS', 'What are the typical difficulty classes and their chances of success?', 'High Chance of Success: 10 or less, Moderate Chance of Success: 15, Low Chance of Success: 20, Almost No Chance of Success: 25 or higher.']\n['ADVANTAGE AND DISADVANTAGE', 'What does it mean to roll with advantage or disadvantage?', 'Rolling with advantage means you roll two d20s and use the higher of the two numbers to calculate your check result. Rolling with disadvantage means you roll two d20s and use the lower of the two numbers to calculate your check result.']\n['ADVANTAGE AND DISADVANTAGE', 'What happens if you have both advantage and disadvantage on a roll?', 'They cancel each other out, and you roll only one d20. This works no matter how many circumstances impose disadvantage or grant advantage.']\n['ADVANTAGE AND DISADVANTAGE', 'Can you reroll both dice if you have advantage or disadvantage and a rule lets you reroll the 