ure of?\", \"An object's AC is a measure of how difficult it is to deal damage to the object by striking it.\"]\n['STATISTICS FOR OBJECTS', \"What is an object's HP a measure of?\", \"An object's HP is a measure of how much damage it can take before losing structural integrity.\"]\n['STATISTICS FOR OBJECTS', 'What are the suggested AC values for various substances?', 'The Object Armor Class table provides suggested AC values for various substances, such as cloth, paper, rope, iron, steel, mithral, and adamantine.']\n['STATISTICS FOR OBJECTS', 'What are the suggested hit point amounts for fragile and resilient objects that are Large or smaller?', 'The Object Hit Points table provides suggested hit point amounts for fragile and resilient objects that are Large or smaller.']\n['STATISTICS FOR OBJECTS', 'How are Huge and Gargantuan objects affected by normal weapons?', 'Normal weapons are of little use against many Huge and Gargantuan objects.']\n['INTERACTING WITH OBJECTS AROUND YOU', 'What are some examples of things a character can do during their move or action?', 'Some examples include drawing or sheathing a sword, opening or closing a door, getting a potion from a backpack, picking up a dropped weapon, taking a bauble from a table, removing a ring from a finger, stuffing food into their mouth, planting a banner in the ground, fishing coins from a belt pouch, drinking ale from a flagon, throwing a lever or switch, pulling a torch from a sconce, extinguishing a small flame, donning a mask, pulling the hood of a cloak up, putting an ear to a door, kicking a small stone, turning a key in a lock, tapping the floor with a 10-foot pole, handing an item to another character, and hitting points.']\n['INTERACTING WITH OBJECTS AROUND YOU', 'Can a character draw or sheathe a sword during their move or action?', 'Yes, drawing or sheathing a sword is one of the examples of things a character can do during their move or action.']\n['INTERACTING WITH OBJECTS AROUND YOU', 'Can a c