 unarmed strike deal?', 'An unarmed strike deals bludgeoning damage equal to 1 + your STR modifier.']\n['OPPORTUNITY ATTACKS', 'What is an opportunity attack?', 'An opportunity attack is a strike you can make when a hostile creature that you can see moves out of your reach.']\n['OPPORTUNITY ATTACKS', 'How do you make an opportunity attack?', 'Use your reaction to make one melee attack against the provoking creature right before it leaves your reach.']\n['OPPORTUNITY ATTACKS', 'How can you avoid provoking an opportunity attack?', 'You can avoid provoking an opportunity attack by taking the Disengage action, teleporting, or being moved by someone or something without using your movement, action, or reaction.']\n['TWO-WEAPON FIGHTING', 'What is the Two-Weapon Fighting rule?', 'When you take the Attack action and attack with a light melee weapon in one hand, you can use a bonus action to attack with a different light melee weapon in the other hand.']\n['TWO-WEAPON FIGHTING', 'Do you add your ability modifier to the damage of the bonus attack in Two-Weapon Fighting?', 'You do not add your ability modifier to the damage of the bonus attack unless your modifier is negative.']\n['GRAPPLING', 'How do you grapple a creature?', \"Using the Attack action, you can make a special melee attack to grapple a creature by making a grapple check (a STR (Athletics) check contested by the target's STR (Athletics) or DEX (Acrobatics) check).\"]\n['GRAPPLING', 'What happens if you win the grapple check?', 'If you win the grapple check, you subject the target to the grappled condition, which specifies what ends it. You can release the target whenever you like.']\n['GRAPPLING', 'How can a grappled creature escape?', 'A grappled creature can use its action to escape by succeeding on a STR (Athletics) or DEX (Acrobatics) check contested by your STR (Athletics) check.']\n['GRAPPLING', 'What happens when you move a grappled creature?', 'When you move, you can drag or carry the grappled creature 