ward.']\n['SERVICES', 'What is the difference between skilled and untrained hirelings?', 'Skilled hirelings are employed to perform a service that involves a proficiency, such as a mercenary, artisan, or scribe, while untrained hirelings are hired for menial work that requires no particular skill, such as laborers, porters, and maids.']\n['MAGIC ITEMS', 'What are magic items and why are they valuable?', 'Magic items are powerful objects created using raw magic that are incredibly complicated to produce, making them hard to find and valuable.']\n['MAGIC ITEMS', 'Who decides where magic items appear?', 'The GM is the ultimate arbiter of where magic items appear, but they are often given as rewards for completing quests or defeating powerful enemies.']\n['USING A MAGIC ITEM', \"How do you use a magic item's properties?\", \"Using a magic item's properties might involve wearing or wielding it in the intended fashion, such as donning armor, strapping a shield to the arm, or holding a weapon.\"]\n['USING A MAGIC ITEM', 'Can magic items adjust to fit creatures of different sizes or builds?', 'In most cases, a magic item meant to be worn can fit a creature regardless of size or build, as many magic garments are made to be easily adjustable or magically adjust themselves to the wearer.']\n['USING A MAGIC ITEM', 'What happens when a nonhumanoid tries to wear a magic item?', \"When a nonhumanoid tries to wear an item, it is up to the GM's discretion as to whether the item functions as intended, as some items may only fit creatures of a certain size or shape.\"]\n['MULTIPLE ITEMS OF THE SAME KIND', 'Can a character wear more than one of a given kind of magic item?', 'Normally, a character can only wear one pair of footwear, one pair of gloves or gauntlets, one pair of bracers, one suit of armor, one item of headwear, and one cloak, but exceptions can be made in certain cases.']\n['PAIRED ITEMS', 'How do paired magic items work?', 'Paired items, such as boots, bracers, gauntlets