 would be treated as a 10.']\n['DUNGEONEER', 'What is the penalty to your passive Perception score when traveling at a fast pace without the Dungeoneer talent?', 'Without the Dungeoneer talent, traveling at a fast pace imposes a -5 penalty to your passive Perception score.']\n['FIELD MEDIC', 'How many times can you use the Field Medic talent to tend to the wounds of a creature?', 'You can use the Field Medic talent to tend to the wounds of a creature once per short or long rest.']\n['POLYGLOT', 'Can you use the Polyglot talent to understand any written language?', \"You can use the Polyglot talent to add your PB to ability checks related to understanding the meaning of a verbal or written language you don't know, doubling your PB if you have proficiency in a relevant skill or tool.\\n1\"]\n['LUCK', 'How do PCs gain Luck points?', 'They gain 1 Luck point once per turn when they fail an attack roll or save, or when the GM awards them for clever ideas, excellent roleplaying, or pursuing interesting choices.']\n['LUCK', 'What is the maximum number of Luck points a PC can have at one time?', '5.']\n['LUCK', 'What happens if a PC has 5 Luck points and would gain a 6th point?', 'They must immediately roll a d4 and reset their Luck points to the die result.']\n['LUCK', 'How can Luck points be spent?', 'Luck points can be spent to add to any d20 roll, or to reroll a d20 after a check is made.']\n['LUCK', 'How many Luck points does it cost to add to a d20 roll?', 'It costs 1 Luck point to add to a d20 roll.']\n['LUCK', 'How many Luck points does it cost to reroll a d20 after a check is made?', 'It costs 3 Luck points to reroll a d20 after a check is made.']\n['LUCK', 'Can Luck points offset the effects of a natural 1 or create a natural 20?', 'No, Luck points cannot offset the effects of a natural 1 or create a natural 20.']\n['TOUCH OF LUCK', 'What are the benefits of the Touch of Luck talent?', 'When you would gain 1 Luck point as a result of failing an attack roll or save,