 check or save to remain in the saddle or is subjected to an effect that would dismount it, the Pegasus can shift to catch the falling rider, preventing the rider from being dismounted.\"]\n['OWLBEAR', 'What are Pegasi like?', 'Pegasi are free-spirited creatures that soar the skies with wild dignity. They are comfortable only in the presence of their own kind and take wing quickly to find more secluded surroundings when intruders are near.']\n['OWLBEAR', 'What do Pegasi eat?', 'Pegasi have a diet similar to mundane horses, feeding on grass and flowers in alpine meadows and taking water from mountain streams and high lakes.']\n['OWLBEAR', 'Where do Pegasi build their nests?', 'Pegasi build nests in rocky hills, atop spires and peaks inaccessible to most creatures without the power of flight.']\n['OWLBEAR', 'How do Pegasi protect their young?', 'Pegasi are fiercely protective of their young and build nests in inaccessible locations. When the young are ready to leave the nest, the entire herd watches over and protects them until they reach adulthood.']\n['OWLBEAR', 'Can Pegasi be tamed?', 'Pegasi are intelligent, autonomous, and untamable. However, a being of pure heart and good intent can sometimes convince a Pegasus to become its companion, especially if the being is in desperate need or faces some monumental task.\\n1']\n['PURPLE WORM', \"What is the purple worm's hunting ground?\", 'The Underworld.']\n['PURPLE WORM', 'What special ability does the purple worm have that allows it to create new tunnels and passageways?', 'Tunneler.']\n['PURPLE WORM', 'What attracts purple worms?', 'Sound and vibration.']\n['PURPLE WORM', 'What do purple worms eat?', 'Any creature besides another of its kind.']\n['PURPLE WORM', \"What can brave souls find among a purple worm's waste or inside its body?\", 'Undigested gems and unrefined ores.']\n['PURPLE WORM', \"What is the purple worm's Armor Class?\", '18 (natural armor).']\n['PURPLE WORM', 'How many hit points does the purple worm 