 the final step in making a check?', 'The GM compares the check result to the check DC and declares whether the check succeeds or fails.']\n['ABILITY MODIFIERS', 'How many ability modifiers are there in the game?', 'There are six ability modifiers: Strength (STR), Dexterity (DEX), Constitution (CON), Wisdom (WIS), Intelligence (INT), and Charisma (CHA).']\n['ABILITY MODIFIERS', 'What is the purpose of ability modifiers?', 'Ability modifiers are added to every check to determine the check result.']\n['ABILITY MODIFIERS', 'Who decides which ability modifier to use for a particular check?', 'The rules typically dictate which modifier to use, but in cases where no ability is listed, the GM decides which one is relevant.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What is the proficiency bonus?', 'The proficiency bonus is a bonus that all PCs and monsters have, which is determined by their level.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'How is the proficiency bonus used?', 'The proficiency bonus is added to a die roll or DC once, even if multiple rules allow you to add it to the same roll.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What happens if a circumstance suggests that your proficiency bonus applies more than once to the same roll?', 'You still add it only once and double or halve it only once.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', \"What happens if your proficiency bonus doesn't apply to a roll?\", \"Doubling your proficiency bonus doesn't change that.\"]\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What is the purpose of the proficiency bonus?', \"The proficiency bonus represents your character's skill and experience in various areas.\"]\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'Do monsters have a proficiency bonus?', 'Yes, monsters also have a proficiency bonus, which is incorporated into their stat blocks.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'Can you add your proficiency bonus to a roll if you lack proficiency in the relevant skill?', 'No, you can only add your proficiency bonus to a roll if you have proficiency in the relevant skill.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'What happe