 Throws represent a creature's ability to resist certain effects, such as spells or abilities. They are made by rolling a d20 and adding the creature's ability modifier and any bonuses or penalties from abilities, spells, or other sources.\"]\n['ELEMENTS OF A STAT BLOCK', 'What are Skills, and how are they used?', \"Skills represent a creature's proficiency in certain tasks. They are made by rolling a d20 and adding the creature's ability modifier and any bonuses or penalties from abilities, spells, or other sources.\"]\n['ELEMENTS OF A STAT BLOCK', 'What are Senses, and how do they work?', \"Senses represent a creature's ability to perceive its surroundings. They include sight, hearing, smell, taste, and touch.\"]\n['ELEMENTS OF A STAT BLOCK', 'What are Languages, and how are they used?', \"Languages represent a creature's ability to communicate with other creatures. They are listed in the Languages heading of a stat block.\"]\n['ELEMENTS OF A STAT BLOCK', 'What is the Challenge Rating (CR) of a creature, and how is it determined?', \"Challenge Rating (CR) represents the difficulty of a creature in combat. It is determined by the creature's abilities, hit points, and other factors.\"]\n['ELEMENTS OF A STAT BLOCK', 'What are Traits, Actions, Reactions, and Legendary Actions, and how are they used?', 'Traits are special abilities that a creature possesses. Actions are things that a creature can do on its turn. Reactions are things that a creature can do outside of its turn. Legendary Actions are special abilities that legendary creatures can use.']\n['CATEGORIES', 'What is the purpose of categories in creature types?', 'Categories denote that creatures are more closely related to each other than they are to other creatures of the same creature type.']\n['CATEGORIES', 'Do categories have any game rules associated with them?', 'No, categories do not have any game rules that reference or rely on them.']\n['CATEGORIES', 'How can categories be helpful?', 'Categories can b