ts and where do they appear in a stat block?', \"Traits are a creature's special characteristics that are likely to be relevant in combat and appear after a creature's ability modifiers but before any actions.\"]\n['ACTIONS', 'What options does a creature have when taking its action?', 'A creature can choose from the options in the Actions section of its stat block or use one of the actions available to all creatures, such as the Dash or Hide action.']\n['MELEE AND RANGED ATTACKS', 'What are the most common actions that a creature takes in combat?', 'The most common actions that a creature takes in combat are melee and ranged attacks, which can be spell attacks or weapon attacks.']\n['MELEE AND RANGED ATTACKS', 'What is a melee attack?', 'A melee attack is an attack made with a weapon that requires the attacker to be within reach of the target.']\n['MELEE AND RANGED ATTACKS', 'What is a ranged attack?', 'A ranged attack is an attack made with a weapon that can be used to target a creature at a distance.']\n['MELEE AND RANGED ATTACKS', 'What is a spell attack?', 'A spell attack is an attack made with a spell that requires the attacker to make an attack roll.']\n['MELEE AND RANGED ATTACKS', 'What is a weapon attack?', 'A weapon attack is an attack made with a weapon that requires the attacker to make an attack roll.']\n['MELEE AND RANGED ATTACKS', 'What is the difference between a spell attack and a weapon attack?', 'A spell attack is made with a spell, while a weapon attack is made with a weapon.\\n1']\n['MELEE OR RANGED ATTACK', 'What is the difference between a target and a creature?', 'A target can be a creature, object, or structure, while a creature is a living being.']\n['MELEE OR RANGED ATTACK', 'Why does the designator \"Creature vs. Target\" exist?', \"It reflects the creature's natural inclination and helps determine if the creature is likely to strategically attack objects or structures.\"]\n['HIT', 'What information is provided after the \"Hit', 'Any dama