ED USAGE', 'What does \"X/Day\" mean in terms of a creature\\'s abilities?', '\"X/Day\" means a special ability can be used a limited number of times in a day, where X is a number (often 1 or 3). The creature must finish a long rest to regain expended uses.']\n['LIMITED USAGE', 'How does the \"Recharge X-Y\" notation work?', '\"Recharge X-Y\" means a creature can use a special ability once. Afterward, the ability has a random chance of recharging during each round of combat. At the start of each of the creature\\'s turns, a d6 is rolled, and if the result is in the range of numbers in the recharge notation, the creature regains the use of the special ability.']\n['LIMITED USAGE', 'What does \"Recharge after a Short or Long Rest\" mean?', '\"Recharge after a Short or Long Rest\" means that a creature can use a special ability once and then must finish a short or long rest to use it again.']\n['LIMITED USAGE', 'What does \"Conditional\" mean in terms of a creature\\'s abilities?', '\"Conditional\" covers situations where an ability can be used only after a certain condition is met. This information always appears in parentheses.']\n['EQUIPMENT', 'Does a stat block typically refer to equipment other than armor or weapons?', 'Rarely, a stat block may refer to equipment other than armor or weapons.']\n['EQUIPMENT', 'What is assumed about creatures that customarily wear clothes?', 'Creatures that customarily wear clothes, such as Humanoids, are assumed to be dressed appropriately.']\n['EQUIPMENT', 'Can a GM equip creatures with additional gear?', 'Yes, a GM can equip creatures with additional gear and weapons.']\n['EQUIPMENT', 'What is the purpose of the Equipment section in a stat block?', \"The Equipment section in a stat block provides information about the creature's armor and weapons, and occasionally other gear.\\n1\"]\n['LEGENDARY CREATURES', 'What are legendary actions?', 'Special actions that a legendary creature can take outside its turn.']\n['LEGENDARY CREATURE