e and raise their young?', 'Hippogriffs mate for life and raise one to two young at a time. They lay eggs and take turns watching over them or the hatchlings while the other mate hunts for food.']\n['HIPPOGRIFF', \"What happens when a hippogriff's rider dies?\", \"When a hippogriff's rider dies, the mount often starves itself to death.\"]\n['HIPPOGRIFF', 'How much is a hippogriff egg worth, and why are they valuable?', 'A single hippogriff egg is valued at 2,000 gp. Hippogriff eggs are prized treasures and valuable to everyone from elven lords to powerful human generals because they are the easiest of all monstrous mounts to train.']\n['HIPPOGRIFF', \"What are the hippogriff's ability scores?\", 'The hippogriff has the following ability scores: STR +3, DEX +1, CON +1, INT -4, WIS +3, CHA -1.']\n['HIPPOGRIFF', 'What special ability does the hippogriff have related to sight?', 'The hippogriff has Heightened Sight, which gives it a Perception of 18 when perceiving by sight.']\n['HIPPOGRIFF', 'What resistance does the hippogriff have?', 'The hippogriff is resistant to exhaustion and to the frightened condition.']\n['HIPPOGRIFF', 'How many attacks does the hippogriff make with its Multiattack action?', 'The hippogriff makes one Beak attack and one Claws attack with its Multiattack action.']\n['HIPPOGRIFF', \"What damage does the hippogriff's Beak attack deal?\", \"The hippogriff's Beak attack deals 8 (1d10 + 3) piercing damage on a hit.\"]\n['HIPPOGRIFF', \"What damage does the hippogriff's Claws attack deal?\", \"The hippogriff's Claws attack deals 10 (2d6 + 3) slashing damage on a hit.\"]\n['HIPPOGRIFF', \"What is the hippogriff's Dive ability, and how does it work?\", 'The hippogriff can use its Dive ability as a bonus action while flying. It moves at least 20 feet in a straight line toward a creature it can see. The target must succeed on a DC 13 STR save or take 7 (2d6) bludgeoning damage and be knocked prone. The ability recharges after 5-6 rounds.']\n['KOBOLD', 'W