ad.']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's Armor Class?\", '13 (barding scraps).']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's speed?\", '60 feet.']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What type of damage does the warhorse skeleton's shortsword attack deal?\", 'Piercing damage.']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What type of damage does the warhorse skeleton's shortbow attack deal?\", 'Piercing damage.\\n1']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's False Appearance ability?\", 'While motionless and prone, it is indistinguishable from an inanimate warhorse skeleton.']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's Undead Nature ability?\", \"It doesn't require air, food, drink, or sleep.\"]\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's Undead Resilience ability?\", 'It is immune to poison damage, exhaustion, and the poisoned condition.']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's Hooves attack?\", 'Melee Weapon Attack: +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 11 (2d6 + 4) bludgeoning damage.']\n['WARHORSE SKELETON', \"What is the warhorse skeleton's Counterattack ability?\", 'When a creature within 5 feet hits it with a melee attack, it can make one Hooves attack against the attacker. (Recharges on a 6)']\n['SPOREBORN', 'What is the origin of the sporeborn?', 'They are humanoid creatures transformed by an infectious fungus that takes control of victims to spread its spores.']\n['SPOREBORN', 'How can humanoids become infected with the apocalyptic fungus?', 'Through contaminated food or water, breathing spore clouds, or the bite of an infected host.']\n['SPOREBORN', 'What are the stages of infection for creatures infected by the apocalyptic fungus?', 'They go through different stages before ultimately expiring, with most dying before reaching the final stage.']\n['SPOREBORN', 'What happens to the host body after it dies from the infection?', \"The fungus continues to grow, dissolving the host's remains, a