AY', 'How does Color Spray affect creatures?', 'Creatures are affected in ascending order of their current hit points, and those with the lowest hit points are blinded until the spell ends.']\n['DIVINE FAVOR', 'How does Divine Favor work?', 'The target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one save of its choice, either before or after making the save.']\n['REGIONAL EFFECTS', \"How does Incited Rage affect creatures near a red dragon's lair?\", \"Creatures within 3 miles of the lair have disadvantage on CHA checks, except CHA (Intimidation), and Beasts in the area that aren't domesticated become more aggressive.\"]\n['MIRROR IMAGE', 'How does Mirror Image protect you from attacks?', \"Each time a creature targets you with an attack during the spell's duration, you roll a d20 to determine whether the attack instead targets one of your duplicates.\"]\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'How does PB improve as a character advances in levels?', 'Every class advances at the same rate, and the progression is listed in each class Progression table for convenience.']\n['ADDITIONAL SPELL DESCRIPTIONS', 'How does Poisonous Fog move?', 'It moves 10 feet away from the caster at the start of each of their turns, rolling along the surface of the ground and sinking to the lowest level of the land.']\n['RICOCHET SHOT', 'How does Ricochet Shot affect the attack roll and damage?', \"You make an attack roll against the target's AC as if it weren't behind cover. On a hit, the target takes damage as if hit by your attack.\"]\n['INTERACTING WITH OBJECTS', 'How does a character interact with objects in an environment?', 'The player tells the GM what their character is doing, and the GM describes what happens.']\n['MYCOLID COMMONER', 'How does a commoner mycolid become a spore lord?', 'When a safe area of rich, damp fertilizer can be secured, a commoner mycolid may undergo a rapid change into a spore lord.']\n['CONE', 'How does a cone spell expand?', 'It extends in a direction chosen by the caster