ers?', 'Ability modifiers are the most important part of your ability scores. You use your modifiers much more than your score to calculate success or failure in the game.']\n['ANIMATED OBJECTS', 'What are animated objects?', 'Nonmagical objects given life by a spellcaster.']\n['SPOREBORN', 'What are bloatblossoms?', 'Skullblooms eventually grow into bloatblossoms, with a riot of fungal growth making their bodies broad and ungainly, and layers of tough, fibrous growth protecting them from damage.']\n['CHARGES', 'What are charges on a magic item?', 'Charges are a limited number of uses that a magic item has before it needs to be recharged.']\n['CIRCLES OF MAGIC', 'What are circles of magic?', 'Circles of magic represent primary sources that fuel spellcaster abilities.']\n['LIFE DOMAIN', 'What are devotees of the Life Domain encouraged to do?', 'They are encouraged to heal the wounded, care for the sick, and oppose the perversion of undeath.']\n['DOMAIN SPELLS', 'What are domain spells, and how do they work?', \"Each cleric subclass has a list of domain spells that the cleric gains access to as soon as they can cast spells of that ring. These spells are always prepared and don't count against the number of spells the cleric can prepare each day.\"]\n['IMPROVISED WEAPONS', 'What are improvised weapons?', 'Improvised weapons are objects that can be wielded as weapons, such as broken glass, a table leg, a frying pan, a wagon wheel, or a dead goblin.']\n['KOBOLD', 'What are kobolds like, and how do they view life?', 'Kobolds are diligent, hardworking creatures who view life through a practical lens. They instinctively conform to the wishes of anyone stronger than themselves rather than risk confrontation.']\n['KOBOLD', 'What are kobolds skilled at, and how do they protect their warrens?', 'Kobolds are skilled miners and inordinately clever with mechanical devices. They routinely surround their warrens with traps, deadfalls, and camouflage.']\n['LAIR ACTIONS', 'What are la