 speed can move through sand, earth, mud, or ice.']\n['SPEED', 'What is a creature with a climbing speed able to do?', \"A creature with a climbing speed can move on vertical surfaces with no check required and doesn't need to spend extra movement to climb.\"]\n['SPEED', 'What is a creature with a flying speed able to do?', 'A creature with a flying speed can move by flying. Some creatures can hover, which makes them hard to knock out of the air.']\n['SPEED', 'What is a creature with a swimming speed able to do?', \"A creature with a swimming speed can move easily through liquid and doesn't need to spend extra movement to swim.\"]\n['SPACE', \"What is a creature's space?\", \"A creature's space is the area in feet that it effectively controls in combat.\"]\n['SPEED', \"What is a creature's walking speed called?\", \"A creature's walking speed is simply called speed.\"]\n['OBJECTS', 'What is a damage threshold, and how does it affect objects?', 'A damage threshold is extra resilience represented by a number. An object with a damage threshold ignores any single attack that deals damage less than its damage threshold.']\n['DEATH SAVES', 'What is a death save?', 'A death save is a special save that a creature must make when it starts its turn with 0 hit points to determine whether it creeps closer to death or hangs onto life.']\n['GROUP CHECKS', 'What is a group check?', \"When a number of individuals try to accomplish something as a group, the GM might ask for a group check, where characters who are skilled at a particular task help cover those who aren't.\"]\n['EQUIPMENT', 'What is a holy symbol used for?', 'A holy symbol is used as a spellcasting focus for clerics.']\n['LAIRS', 'What is a lair?', 'A special location where a legendary creature spends a great deal of time and can create special effects.']\n['RESTING', 'What is a long rest, and how long does it last?', 'A long rest is a period of extended downtime, at least 8 hours long, during which a character sleeps 