', 'DOOM\\n Q', \"The GM can spend Doom to give a creature advantage on an attack roll, give a PC disadvantage on a save, or once per encounter, refresh, recharge, or otherwise gain one additional use of a limited-use feature, such as a dragon's Breath Weapon, a legendary creature's Legendary Resistance, or a spell in a mage's Spellcasting.\"]\n['OPTIONAL RULE', 'DOOM\\n Q', 'The Doom tiers are as follows: 0-4: 5 Doom; 5-8: 9 Doom; 9-12: 13 Doom; 13-16: 17 Doom; 17-20: 21 Doom; 21+: HDym;~R][W)rmo].']\n['CATEGORIES', 'Do categories have any game rules associated with them?', 'No, categories do not have any game rules that reference or rely on them.']\n['CLERIC SPELLCASTING', 'Do clerics need to prepare ritual spells?', 'No, they do not need to prepare ritual spells.']\n['PROFICIENCY BONUS', 'Do monsters have a proficiency bonus?', 'Yes, monsters also have a proficiency bonus, which is incorporated into their stat blocks.']\n['CLERIC SPELLCASTING', 'Do ritual spells use up spell slots?', 'No, they do not use up spell slots.']\n['CLERIC SPELLCASTING', 'Do rituals count against the number of spells a cleric can learn at each level?', 'No, they do not count against the number of spells a cleric can learn at each level.\\n1']\n['TWO-WEAPON FIGHTING', 'Do you add your ability modifier to the damage of the bonus attack in Two-Weapon Fighting?', 'You do not add your ability modifier to the damage of the bonus attack unless your modifier is negative.']\n['RANGED WEAPON MASTERY', 'Do you have disadvantage on ranged weapon attacks made at long range without Ranged Weapon Mastery?', 'Yes, without Ranged Weapon Mastery, you would have disadvantage on ranged weapon attacks made at long range.']\n['SPELL TARGETS', 'Do you need to have a clear path to the target to cast a spell?', \"Yes, you must have a clear path to the target, so it can't be behind total cover.\"]\n['LEVEL ADVANCEMENT', 'Do you reset the XP total after each level?', 'No, you keep piling it on.']\n['RICOCHET SHOT'