IMATED ARMOR', 'What are the immunities and resistances of the animated armor?', 'It is immune to poison and psychic damage, and it is resistant to piercing damage.']\n['CRIMSON JELLY', 'What are the immunities and resistances of the crimson jelly?', 'It is resistant to the grappled and restrained conditions, and it is immune to exhaustion, the blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, and prone conditions.']\n['FLYING SWORD', 'What are the immunities and resistances of the flying sword?', 'It is immune to poison and psychic damage, and it is resistant to piercing damage.']\n['KOBOLD', \"What are the kobold's weapon attacks?\", 'Dagger (melee, +4 to hit, 4 piercing damage) and Sling (ranged, +4 to hit, 4 bludgeoning damage).']\n['1ST-RING DIVINE (EVOCATION)', 'What are the limitations of \"Healing Word\"?', 'It has a range of 60 feet and can only target a creature that the caster can see. Additionally, it has no effect on Undead or Constructs.']\n['CONTINUAL FLAME', 'What are the limitations of Continual Flame?', \"It creates no heat, doesn't use oxygen, and can be covered or hidden but not smothered or quenched.\"]\n['MIRROR IMAGE', 'What are the limitations of Mirror Image?', \"The spell ends when all three duplicates are destroyed, and a creature is unaffected by the spell if it can't see, relies on senses other than sight, or can perceive illusions as false, such as with truesight.\"]\n['REVIVIFY', 'What are the limitations of Revivify?', 'It can only revive a creature that has died within the last minute, and it cannot restore any missing body parts or bring back a creature that died of old age.']\n['SPEAK WITH DEAD', 'What are the limitations of Speak with Dead?', 'The corpse must still have a mouth, cannot be Undead, and cannot have been the target of this spell within the last 10 days.']\n['SPEAK WITH ANIMALS', 'What are the limitations of communicating with Beasts using Speak with Animals?', 'Their knowledge and awareness are limited by their INT, and they ca